Jane Furse Hospital in Limpopo has been hit by heavy
floods following heavy rains in the area. Patients had to be
relocated to other facilities following a huge storm. Health spokesperson in Limpopo Neil Shikwambana said the
storm caused serious flooding and damages to some component of the hospital
which necessitated that patients be evacuated to nearby facilities such as St
Ritas. He said MEC Health Phophi Ramathuba will visit the
hospital to assess the extent of damages and the inconvenience caused. 